content:
Give your policyholders access to view and change important information about their account, policies, claims, and billing options with the Policyholder Digital Experience site. We provide you with a site template and a set of components to get you started.

To use the Policyholder site template, you must install the Insurance FSC Unmanaged Package. You can brand the components with your colors, fonts, logo, and other styles. To learn how, see Digital Experience Site Component Customization Overview.

The Policyholder site template contains top-level pages:

* Policyholder Digital Experience Site Home Page
* Policyholder Digital Experience Site Policies Page
* Policyholder Digital Experience Site Billing Page
* Policyholder Digital Experience Site Claims Page

Here's an overview of the components we included in the template, and how they fit together:

* Home: Displays a summary of the policyholder's information.
* Policies: Displays a list of policies associated with the policyholder's account.
* Policy Details and Policy FSC Details components are used for specific pages.
* Billing: Provides information about the policyholder's billing account.
* What's Next: Offers options to proceed with further actions.
* Claims: Displays a list of claim records associated with the policyholder's account.

The Policyholder site contains a bunch of components to get you started with providing your policyholders with functionality they can use to self-manage some parts of their policies.
title: Policyholder Digital Experience Site
